---
// FeeStructure.astro
// 1.5% management fee + 15% performance fee with high-watermark
// Source: research/10 fee structure, SPA_ARCHITECTURE_EVOLUTION_v2.md §3.4
// Note: research doc says 1% (Phase 1) — 1.5% appears in user prompt.
// Using 1.5% mgmt + 15% perf as specified in the build task.
---

<section id="fees" class="py-24 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 bg-[#0d1117]">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">

    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="mb-12 max-w-2xl">
      <p class="text-white/30 text-sm font-mono uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Fee Structure</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4 leading-tight">
        Simple, Aligned, Transparent
      </h2>
      <p class="text-white/50 leading-relaxed">
        Fees are designed so we only win significantly when you win.
        The high-watermark means we never collect performance fees on recovered losses.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Fee cards -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-10">

      <!-- Management fee -->
      <div class="rounded-2xl bg-white/4 border border-white/10 p-8">
        <div class="text-4xl font-mono font-bold text-white mb-2">1.5%</div>
        <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-white/70 mb-4">Annual Management Fee</div>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/40 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Charged annually on assets under management. Covers infrastructure, strategy
          development, monitoring, and investor reporting.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-white/40">
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="text-teal-400">✓</span>
            Accrued daily, settled at period end
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="text-teal-400">✓</span>
            0% during paper trading period
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="text-teal-400">✓</span>
            Competitive vs. market (1–2% standard)
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Performance fee -->
      <div class="rounded-2xl bg-accent-500/5 border border-accent-500/20 p-8">
        <div class="text-4xl font-mono font-bold text-accent-400 mb-2">15%</div>
        <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-white/70 mb-4">Performance Fee <span class="text-accent-400/60 text-xs font-normal">+ High-Water Mark</span></div>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/40 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          15% of net profits above the high-water mark. If the portfolio declines, no
          performance fee is charged until the previous peak is recovered.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-white/40">
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="text-accent-400">✓</span>
            High-watermark: no double-charging on recoveries
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="text-accent-400">✓</span>
            Below market: industry standard 20%
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="text-accent-400">✓</span>
            Only on net gains — losses reduce the base
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- High watermark explanation -->
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-white/8 bg-white/2 p-6 mb-8">
      <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-white mb-3">How the High-Water Mark Works</h3>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-6 text-sm">
        <div>
          <div class="text-white/30 uppercase tracking-wider text-[10px] font-mono mb-2">Example start</div>
          <div class="text-white/70">Portfolio: $100,000</div>
          <div class="text-white/40 text-xs mt-1">High-water mark set at $100K</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="text-white/30 uppercase tracking-wider text-[10px] font-mono mb-2">Year 1: +8%</div>
          <div class="text-white/70">Portfolio: $108,000</div>
          <div class="text-white/40 text-xs mt-1">Perf fee: 15% × $8K = $1,200. HWM → $108K</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="text-white/30 uppercase tracking-wider text-[10px] font-mono mb-2">Year 2: flat recovery</div>
          <div class="text-white/70">Portfolio recovers to $108K</div>
          <div class="text-white/40 text-xs mt-1">No performance fee — HWM not exceeded</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Comparison callout -->
    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center gap-4 rounded-xl border border-teal-500/20 bg-teal-500/5 p-5">
      <div class="text-teal-400 flex-shrink-0">
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" aria-hidden="true">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="m11.25 11.25.041-.02a.75.75 0 0 1 1.063.852l-.708 2.836a.75.75 0 0 0 1.063.853l.041-.021M21 12a9 9 0 1 1-18 0 9 9 0 0 1 18 0Zm-9-3.75h.008v.008H12V8.25Z"/>
        </svg>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-white/50">
        Industry comparison: Yearn charges 2% mgmt + 20% perf. Maple: 0.7–0.9% all-in.
        SPA at <strong class="text-white/70">1.5% + 15%</strong> is below the hedge fund standard
        while covering the operational cost of a deterministic autonomous system.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
